          "evidence_text_excerpt": "8\n15. Quiet Period\nIn order to avoid any potential for, or the perception or appearance of selective disclosure, the\nBank observes a \u201cquiet period\u201d. The quiet period commences on the first day following the end of\nthe reporting period until the release of that quarter\u2019s results. During the quiet period, all\nspokespersons will exercise caution to avoid selective disclosure of any MNPI (which includes\nnon-public earnings targets and information and financial performance). Communication with\nanalysts, investors, market professionals or the media will be limited to responding to inquiries\nabout publicly available or non- material information, unless it has been determined by the\nDisclosure Committee that disclosure is appropriate, in which case, disclosure will be made in\naccordance with this Disclosure Policy.\nIf the Bank is invited to participate in investor community meetings or",
